result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathanael Terrence Stubbs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Penalty - Retail Theft (<=$500), Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: May be served under the Huber Law as long as the defendant reports and remains alcohol and controlled substance free.

Failure to pay will be judgment in favor of Creditor against Debtor until paid in full. 
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample by calling the Green County Jail Office at (608) 328-9598 WITHIN 72 HOURS OF SENTENCING to set up an appointment.  The Jail Office hours are 8 a.m. - 4 p.m. Monday - Friday.  Defendant shall provide proof of identification along with the Judgment of Conviction documenting a DNA Surcharge.  Failure to comply with this order may result in either a finding of contempt of court or a criminal charge of Failure to Provide a DNA Sample pursuant to Wis. Stats. 946.52
Failure to pay will be judgment in favor of Creditor against Debtor until paid in full.
